    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation - Crankshaft Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.4.4" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Crankshaft Assembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure crankshaft assembly has been inspected per instructions in this section before
                    proceeding.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a lint-free cloth to wipe upper crankcase assembly bearing supports free of oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each bearing. Replace scored, chipped or worn bearings.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When inserting main bearings, make sure oil is not between back side of bearing and upper
                    crankcase assembly bearing saddles.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure upper thrust bearing is installed at number four upper main bearing journal.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place upper main bearings in upper crankcase assembly. Make sure locking tabs on bearings
                are snapped in saddle and oil holes in bearings line up with oil holes in upper crankcase assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015028" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0717.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Upper main bearings lubrication</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate bearings with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate camshaft so timing mark on camshaft gear is pointing upwards.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015029" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07116.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lifting sling</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifting sling</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a correct size lifting sling and hoist with a safety
                    latch on hook.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not bend, drop or mar crankshaft.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a bolt in each end of the crankshaft assembly (if removed). Attach hoist and lifting
                sling around crankshaft bolts and lower it onto five main bearings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07113.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft and camshaft timing marks</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install crankshaft so timing mark on gear aligns with timing mark on camshaft gear.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
